: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FEDDFA52FDD55170" box="[364,536,1530,1557]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">São Paulo State</collectingRegion>
, Cotia, Jardim Barbacena; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF8FF91FCF0FA53FC275170" box="[833,1002,1530,1557]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="2019-03-25">25 March 2019</date>
, 1347 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF8FF91FB80FA52FB915170" box="[1073,1116,1531,1557]" country="USA" name="Pratt Museum" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">PM</collectionCode>
; 
<collectionCode id="ED12AE03FFF8FF91FBD7FA52FBB65170" box="[1126,1147,1531,1557]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">R</collectionCode>
. Lazaro. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FA91FA52FA6C5170" box="[1312,1441,1531,1557]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Corinna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF8FF91FA91FA52FAB65170" box="[1312,1403,1531,1557]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Corinna</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FF79F9B5FE835152" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1880" box="[200,334,1564,1591]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Corinnidae</taxonomicName>
), adult or subadult female. Four photographs show the wasp cutting off the legs of the immobilized corinnid sac spider at the coxa-trochanter joints and discarding them on the substrate as it laid dorsal or ventral side upward (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF8FF91FEE7F9F6FE3C511C" author="Lazaro R." box="[342,497,1631,1657]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" refId="ref25196" refString="Lazaro R. 2019 a. Mud-nesting Spiders Wasps (Tribe Ageniellini). Available at https: // www. inaturalist. org / observations / 94353385. (Last accessed 13 September 2021)." type="url" year="2019">Lazaro 2019a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C6FFF8FF91FEB1F928FB3E51BB" blockId="13.[192,1441,1495,1759]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<collectingCountry id="F3147656FFF8FF91FEB1F928FEAF51FE" box="[256,354,1665,1691]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FEDCF928FDD651FE" box="[365,539,1665,1691]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">São Paulo State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F824FFF8FF91FD97F928FD5A51FE" box="[550,663,1665,1691]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
; 
<date id="FFBD1006FFF8FF91FD13F928FC8D51FE" box="[674,832,1665,1691]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" value="2009-03-08">8 March 2009</date>
; G. Grespan. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FBAFF928FB5351FE" box="[1054,1182,1665,1691]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Corinna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B977EAD4FFF8FF91FBAFF928FBB451FE" box="[1054,1145,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Corinna</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D45FFF8FF91FB1CF928FAF951F9" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1880" box="[1197,1332,1665,1692]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Corinnidae</taxonomicName>
). penultimate male. The wasp straddled the immobilized antmimic spider, dorsal side upward, and grasped the base of its left chelicera with her mandibles. The spider’s legs and pedipalps were left intact (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B37FFF8FF91FBF7F96DFB2551BB" author="Grespan G." box="[1094,1256,1732,1758]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" refId="ref23777" refString="Grespan G. 2009. Killer … Available at https: // www. flickr. com / photos / guilhermegrespan / 3347118603 / in / album- 72157604321718087 /. (Last accessed 6 January 2021)." type="url" year="2009">Grespan 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
